; specs/grammar/capability-discovery.abnf
; RFC-0008 — Capability Discovery and Advertisement
; Status: Draft. This grammar is NOT normative until the RFC is Ratified
; (see specs/README.md). Grounding behaviour on a Draft is an error.
;
; This file defines the syntax RFC-0008 owns: the capability identifier
; carried in a CapabilityAdvertisement `capabilities[]` array (and matched
; by an envelope `requirements[]`, RFC-0003), plus the advertisement's
; enum-valued and DID-valued leaf fields and its KV key. The advertisement
; OBJECT itself is a JSON value [RFC8259] signed over its RFC 8785 JCS
; serialization (RFC-0004); its object framing is JSON, not an ABNF token
; grammar, so only the string-typed leaves are given here.
;
; Terminal alphabets (`lower`, `DIGIT`, `did`) are defined ONCE, in
; RFC-0001 (specs/grammar/identifiers.abnf), and referenced here — never
; redefined (grammar/README.md rule 5).
;
; Core rules ALPHA, DIGIT are imported from [RFC5234] Appendix B.
; Case-sensitive string literals (%s"…") are per [RFC7405].
; `lower` and `did` are imported from RFC-0001.

; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
; 1. Capability identifier.  *** OPEN DECISION — Andreas + JC ***
;    The single grammar the discovery wire matches on CANNOT be written
;    until the C-3 reconciliation (RFC §6.1) chooses between the two
;    deployed, MUTUALLY INCOMPATIBLE grammars below. Presented, NOT chosen.
; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

; capability-id — PLACEHOLDER binding. Until the C-3 decision resolves, an
; advertisement's `capabilities[]` entries are UNVALIDATED at the myelin
; signing/verification boundary (RFC §9.1, a Security finding): any JSON
; string is accepted. The two grammars below are what the two live wires
; ACTUALLY enforce ELSEWHERE (the envelope requirements[] side, and cortex's
; parallel agent.capabilities-changed / config side). Neither is endorsed
; here as the target — this rule is transcribed for fidelity, not adopted.
capability-id           = capability-tag / capability-id-compound

; capability-tag — the SINGLE-SEGMENT capability tag. Faithful transcription
; of CAPABILITY_TAG_RE, myelin src/patterns.ts:21
;   /^[a-z](?:[a-z0-9]|-(?!-)){0,62}[a-z0-9]$/
; Semantics: 2–64 chars; first char `lower`; last char alphanumeric;
; interior single hyphens only — NO leading, trailing, or consecutive "-";
; NO "." and NO "_". Single-char tags are FORBIDDEN. This is the grammar the
; envelope `requirements[]` items enforce (RFC-0003, schema line 154) and
; the grammar every task-side capability match is written against.
;
; The 2..64 length bound is a semantic constraint (regex {0,62}); the run
; decomposition below expresses the character and hyphen rules exactly.
capability-tag          = lower 1*tag-sym *( "-" 1*tag-sym )
                        / lower 1*( "-" 1*tag-sym )
tag-sym                 = lower / DIGIT

; capability-id-compound — the DOTTED-COMPOUND capability id. Faithful
; transcription of CAPABILITY_ID_REGEX,
; cortex src/common/types/capability.ts:172
;   /^[a-z][a-z0-9_-]*(\.[a-z][a-z0-9_-]*)*$/
; Semantics: one or more "."-separated segments; each segment starts with
; `lower`, then ANY of [a-z0-9_-]. This grammar ADMITS what capability-tag
; FORBIDS: "_", consecutive hyphens, and trailing hyphens; and "." splits a
; compound id across MULTIPLE NATS subject segments. NO upper length bound.
; This is the grammar cortex's parallel `agent.capabilities-changed` wire
; (cortex src/bus/agent-network/envelopes.ts:102) and its config-side
; offerings enforce; its live ids ("dev.implement",
; "federated.subject_dispatch") are UNEXPRESSIBLE as a capability-tag.
capability-id-compound  = compound-segment *( "." compound-segment )
compound-segment        = lower *( lower / DIGIT / "_" / "-" )

; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
; 2. Advertisement leaf grammars.
; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

; sovereignty-mode — the advertisement's advertised posture AND the envelope
; `sovereignty_required` minimum. Case-sensitive lowercase enum. Transcribes
; SovereigntyMode (myelin src/discovery/types.ts:7) and the schema enum
; (schemas/envelope.schema.json, sovereignty_required). The ORDER these
; four modes impose on a task↔advert match ("minimum" mode) is UNDEFINED in
; source — see OPEN DECISION §6.5.
sovereignty-mode        = %s"open" / %s"selective" / %s"strict" / %s"bidding"

; advertisement-identity — the advertisement actor-DID (CapabilityAdvertisement
; .identity) and the discovery registration stamp DID (signed_by.identity).
; It is a `did` (RFC-0001). The R2 transition window also accepts the
; deprecated `principal` key on READ (advertisement-identity.ts); a record
; carrying BOTH keys is REJECTED with `dual_field_conflict`. myelin EMITS
; only `identity`. This grammar constrains the VALUE, not the key.
advertisement-identity  = did

; advertisement-kv-key — the key an advertisement is stored under in the
; AGENT_CAPABILITIES KV bucket (RFC §5). The SHIPPED store keys by the
; advertisement actor-DID (myelin src/discovery/memory-store.ts:47-52).
; *** OPEN DECISION §6.3 — the informative design doc
; (docs/design-agent-task-routing.md:293-297) keys by agent SHORT-NAME
; ("luna") with a separate `principal` field. The two disagree. ***
advertisement-kv-key    = did
